# ── LLM Provider Configuration ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# The agent auto-detects the provider from whichever API key is set.
# Or set LLM_PROVIDER explicitly to choose one.
#
# Option 1: CBORG (LBL users) — default if CBORG_API_KEY is set
# CBORG_API_KEY=your-cborg-api-key-here

# Option 2: OpenAI
# OPENAI_API_KEY=your-openai-api-key-here

# Option 3: Google Gemini
# GEMINI_API_KEY=your-gemini-api-key-here

# Option 4: Anthropic Claude (direct)
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your-anthropic-api-key-here

# ── Optional LLM overrides ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# LLM_PROVIDER=cborg          # Force a specific provider (cborg/openai/gemini/anthropic)
# MODEL=anthropic/claude-sonnet  # Override the default model for the chosen provider
# LLM_BASE_URL=https://...    # Override the API base URL
# MAX_TOKENS=4096             # Maximum tokens in response

# ── DIALS Configuration ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Path to the DIALS installation bin directory.
# Leave empty or unset if DIALS commands are already on your system PATH
# (e.g., after running `source /path/to/dials/dials_env.sh`).
# DIALS_PATH=/path/to/dials/conda_base/bin/

# ── Data Directories ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Directory containing raw input data (images, HDF5, CBF, etc.).
# The agent will scan this directory to discover data files for import.
# DATA_DIRECTORY=/path/to/raw/data/

# Working directory where DIALS output files will be written.
# Defaults to the current directory if not set.
# WORKING_DIRECTORY=/path/to/output/

# ── Advanced Settings ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# COMMAND_TIMEOUT=3600        # Timeout for DIALS commands in seconds (default: 1 hour)
# LOG_LEVEL=INFO              # Logging level (DEBUG, INFO, WARNING, ERROR)
# LOG_FILE=                   # Log file path (empty for stdout only)
